"Do you want to provide droidfood feedback for Face Unlock? We need data from a diverse set of users using the feature in real-world scenarios to make sure our Face Unlock works equally well for all our users.
If you volunteer to participate, data collected from unlock attempts (e.g. facial imagery) will be made available in the preinstalled Overlay data collection app. Your facial imagery data will be uploaded to and shared with Google ONLY upon your review and explicit consent in the Overlay app. Model performance metadata from unlock attempts will be collected via Android metrics."

"Automatically back up device data (such as Wi-Fi passwords and call history) and app data (such as settings and files stored by apps) to Google Drive.
When you turn on automatic backup, device and app data is periodically saved to a private folder in Google Drive. App data can be any data that an app has saved (based on developer settings), including potentially sensitive data such as contacts, messages, and photos.
Backup data will not count towards your Drive storage quota. Large files, or files developers have chosen to exclude from the service will not be backed up."

"You and your child can delete their face model or turn off Face Unlock at any time in Settings. Face models are stored on the phone until they’re deleted.
Learn more at g.co/pixel/faceunlock."
You and your child are in control

"You can delete your face model or turn off Face Unlock at any time in Settings. Face models are stored on the phone until you delete them.
Learn more at g.co/pixel/faceunlock."

"Face Unlock creates a unique model of your child’s face to verify it’s them. To create this face model during setup, your child will take images of their face from different angles.
When they use Face Unlock, images are used to update their face model. Images used to create their face model are never stored, but the face model is stored securely on the phone and never leaves the phone. All processing occurs securely on the phone."

"Face Unlock creates a unique model of your face to verify it’s you. To create this face model during setup, you will take images of your face from different angles.
When you use Face Unlock, images are used to update your face model. Images used to create your face model are never stored, but the face model is stored securely on your phone and never leaves the phone. All processing occurs securely on your phone."
Face Unlock can require your child’s eyes to be open to unlock the phone or verify it’s them. You and your child can turn this option on at any time in Settings.
If your child normally wears eyeglasses, they can wear them during setup.

Looking at the phone can unlock it even when they don’t intend to. Their phone can also be unlocked by someone who looks a lot like them, like an identical sibling, or if someone holds it up to their face.

In addition to unlocking your phone, you can also use Nexus Imprint to authorize purchases and app access. Learn more
The data recorded by Nexus Imprint is stored securely and never leaves your phone. You can delete your data anytime in Settings.

"Nexus Imprint uses your fingerprint to wake and unlock your phone, authorize purchases, or sign in to apps.
Be careful whose fingerprints you add. Any fingerprints added will be able to do these things. "Learn more

"With Nexus Imprint, you can use your fingerprint to authorize purchases or sign in to apps.
Be careful whose fingerprints you add. Any fingerprints added will be able to do these things.
Note: You can’t use your fingerprint to unlock this device. For more information, contact your organization’s admin."
Pixel Imprint creates a unique model of your fingerprint to verify it’s you. To create this fingerprint model during setup, you will take images of your fingerprint from different positions.
You can delete your fingerprint model, or turn off Pixel Imprint at any time in Settings. Fingerprint models are stored on the phone until you delete them.

Pixel Imprint creates a unique model of your child’s fingerprint to verify it’s them. To create this fingerprint model during setup, they will take images of their fingerprint from different positions.
You and your child can delete their fingerprint model, or turn off Pixel Imprint at any time in Settings. Fingerprint models are stored on the phone until they’re deleted.
